.TH "ata_pci_sff_prepare_host" 9 "ata_pci_sff_prepare_host" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_pci_sff_prepare_host \- helper to prepare PCI PIO-only SFF ATA host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_pci_sff_prepare_host
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct ata_port_info * const *ppi "  ","
.BI "struct ata_host **r_host "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
target PCI device
.IP "ppi" 12
array of port_info, must be enough for two ports
.IP "r_host" 12
out argument for the initialized ATA host

Helper to allocate PIO-only SFF ATA host for \fIpdev\fP, acquire
all PCI resources and initialize it accordingly in one go.

LOCKING:
Inherited from calling layer (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
